    "basmil_text_cards_iHHcHL": {
      "type": "basmil-text-cards",
      "blocks": {
        "content_wJkQhr": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "card_one": "<h3>Consider as you Sign Up</h3><p><strong>Airline tickets :-</strong> Before purchasing your airline tickets, we kindly request that you check with us to ensure the trip has reached the minimum number of participants required for confirmation. This will help avoid any inconvenience or cancellation due to insufficient participants.</p><p><strong>Travel insurance :-</strong> We strongly advise obtaining travel insurance to protect your travel investment. Purchasing travel insurance provides essential protection and peace of mind throughout your journey.</p><p>This will help avoid any inconvenience or cancellation due to insufficient participants.</p>",
            "card_two": "<h3>What’s Included</h3><ul><li>Guided Excursions</li><li>Safety Equipment </li><li>Photography and Filming </li><li>Meals and Accommodation</li><li>Transportation Facilities </li><li>Trekking and Hiking </li><li>Permit Fees<br/></li></ul>"
          }
        },
        "content_RmnRXE": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "card_one": "<h3>Single Travellers</h3><p>Homestay accommodations provide shared rooms, with solo travelers paired with a same-gender roommate for a comfortable stay. Also, hotel stays offer single accommodations, providing privacy and convenience.</p>",
            "card_two": "<h3>Weather</h3><p>In the western region of Lamjung, Nepal, the weather is influenced by varying elevation, slope, and exposure, resulting in rapidly changing conditions. Summer afternoons often bring rain and wind, making it crucial to be prepared for sudden temperature drops of 20 to 30°C and unexpected rainstorms.</p><p> In the alpine areas of Lamjung, there is a notable contrast between daytime and nighttime temperatures. While daytime temperatures typically range from 25 to 30°C, evenings can see a drop to the 20s or low 25s, requiring layers for comfort.<br/></p>"
          }
        },
        "content_dBztXL": {
          "type": "content",
          "settings": {
            "card_one": "<h3>Cancellation and Transfer Policy</h3><p>A $600 refundable deposit is required at booking, and full payment is due 30 days before departure. Cancellation fees apply based on the timing of the cancellation notice.</p><ol><li>91+ days before departure: $100</li><li>61 to 90 days before departure: $200</li><li>31 to 60 days before departure: 50% of the total trip cost is non-refundable.</li><li>Alternatively, if you wish to transfer to another date, the following fees will apply at the time of the request:</li><li>61+ days before departure: $0</li><li>31 to 60 days before departure: $200</li></ol>",
            "card_two": "<h3>Not Included</h3><ul><li>Ticket from your country to Kathmandu</li><li>Guide gratuities, items of a personal nature</li><li>Insurance of any kind</li><li>Alcoholic beverages, Soft drinks</li><li>Insurance of any kind</li></ul>"
          }
        }
      },
